        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 13 at 6:48PM MDT until June 13 at 7:30PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>SVRBOU

The National Weather Service in Denver has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northwestern Logan County in northeastern Colorado...
Northeastern Weld County in northeastern Colorado...

* Until 730 PM MDT.

* At 648 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line from
12 miles south of Kimball Municipal Airport to 5 miles north of
Stoneham, or along a line from 14 miles south of Kimball to 24
miles west of Sterling, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect
hail damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.
Expect wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Westplains.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. These storms are capable of producing damaging winds and
large hail.

Tornadoes can develop quickly from severe thunderstorms. Seek
shelter immediately in an interior room on the lowest floor of a
well-built structure.</instruction>
